<subSubSection id="9F2F7B9591131D0A7823D40189540582" pageId="0" pageNumber="69073" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9217B17B5FF32024F93FC334E3574D94" pageId="0" pageNumber="69073">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="049A9A1BA9771EA1EF48137AF0FE6C32" pageId="0" pageNumber="69073">
We tentatively identified specimens collected in this study as ssp. 
<taxonomicName id="9AF967D51E3FE336F6605A68DD2B88D0" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Tajuria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tajuria sekii subsp. cooperi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="69073" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sekii" subSpecies="cooperi">Tajuria sekii cooperi</taxonomicName>
, with the bluish scales in the centre of fore-wings absent and a relatively limited violet area on hind-wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
